The paper deals with communication over channels, which is a topic in information theory (cs.IT). The use of variable-length coding schemes suggests that the paper may also be related to coding theory (cs.CC). The analysis of state information revealed to the encoder and/or decoder suggests that the paper may be related to signal processing (cs.SI) and data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the characterization of capacities suggests that the paper may also be related to machine learning (cs.LG).
